03/12/2009
ATHENS, Greece -- The 7th meeting of the OSCE Ministerial Council ended in Athens on Wednesday (December 2nd) with a joint declaration, for the first time since 2002. At a press conference afterwards, Greek Prime Minister George Papandreou described the meeting as "a new page in the OSCE's history". Representatives of the previous and upcoming holders of the rotating OSCE presidency -- Finland and Kazakhstan -- also praised Greece's success at the helm. (Ta Nea, BTA - 02/12/09)
